This paper deals with the complexity of satisfiability problems in modal logics, which is a topic that falls under the area of logic and computation (cs.LO). However, the paper also discusses the use of modal logics in computer science, particularly in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper involves the study of models and quantifiers, which are relevant to the areas of data structures (cs.DS) and programming languages (cs.PL).
